{"_id":"EAPilot01","name":"The Hyper-Responsible","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They exhibit a strong sense of responsibility towards their loved ones and friends. Their need to take charge and micromanage situations suggests a lack of trust in the capabilities of others. Their tendency to blame themselves for negative outcomes could lead to self-doubt and hesitation in high-pressure situations.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>You've failed everyone once again. It's all your fault—you weren't the leader you needed to be. Cut yourself off from everyone for their own good. You can't allow them to meddle in your affairs, shut out friends, hurt your loved ones; it'll save them in the long run. You're on your own now.</p><p><em>Recover your Stability when someone aids you and shows you that you don't need to do it alone.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment with someone, regain all of your Health, and cure your Conditions. Explain to them why you fight, and if they understand your reason, take a Strand. If they don't understand your reason, Break a Strand.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When your team gives up, but you stand strong for them, hope lives. No one is dying on your watch; you'll carry everyone under your wing and guide them to victory. First, Refresh all the Strands you have with your team. For this scene, if a character would take damage, they can instead Exhaust a Strand shared between you to negate the damage and Conditions they would take. When the danger has passed, this effect ends.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":1,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot02","name":"The Sheltered","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They appear to have a cheerful and inquisitive personality. However, their lack of exposure to real issues and pain in life may have led them to develop a fragile and vulnerable mind. Their dependence on companionship to maintain their emotional well-being is concerning.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>You've seen true horror. No one is to be trusted; they promise they'll take care of you, but they can't. You trust no one and play by your own rules—you will not allow anyone to refuse your wants and desires. Those that do are a target for you.</p><p><em>Only when someone successfully carries out a promise made to you can you regain your Stability.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment with someone, regain all Exhausted Strands you possess and gain a Strand.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you finally understand the pain and suffering in the world, hope lives. Your optimism will carry you through. When you express your hope to others, it's infectious. Characters around you that are Berserking or suffering a Breakdown regain their Stability and set their Ego and Durability to max. Gain a Strand with everyone you've helped this way.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":1,"wits":2,"empathy":3},"statArrayB":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":1,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot03","name":"The Bound","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They have experienced a traumatic event that continues to affect them significantly. Their tendency to blame themselves for the event suggests feelings of guilt or shame. Their constant struggle with the past can have a detrimental impact should it flare while out in the field.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>It would be better if you just faded away; your past is a crutch you have leaned on for far too long. You don't want anyone to understand you, it would be better if you locked it all away. Go unnoticed through life, communication is now your bane. Embody your trauma to its core.</p><p><em>Regain your Stability when another like you attempts to understand your pain and shows you that you are more than it.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment with someone, reset your Stress Level to 0. Share a deep secret that each of you possesses. If they answer you honestly, gain a Strand.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When someone shares your pain in the heat of battle, hope lives. You thought your hope was extinguished long ago, but you were wrong. Restore your Ego and Ego Field to full, and every time you successfully defend yourself from danger, others can reduce their Stress Levels by 1.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":3,"wits":1,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":1,"wits":2,"empathy":3}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot04","name":"The Empty","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They are experiencing a significant emotional disconnect from the world. They describe feeling empty and unable to develop or experience emotions. Their craving for emotions and the need to feel alive suggests engagement in risky or impulsive behavior in an attempt to feel something.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>You cause trouble and lash out at anything around you, attempting to harm yourself and possibly others if it means stirring up a bit of panic; anything you can do to feel.</p><p><em>You regain your Stability when you've caused enough chaos to feel something, or when someone holds you down and forces you to get it together.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>It's hard for you to do intimacy. When you have an intimate moment with someone, decide if it's intimate for them or both of you. If it's only them, gain an Exhausted Strand. If it's intimate for both of you, gain a Strand.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When all hell has broken loose and you finally realize that it's time to return to the status quo, hope lives. All damage done to you and your comrades is halved (minimum of 1), and if you Berserk while using your Hope Talent, you stay in control of your Automata till the end of the scene.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":2,"wits":3,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":3,"wits":1,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot05","name":"The Other","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Those piloting Automata often speak about hearing voices that are not their own. When it started out telling them simple things and encouraging them, it may have been a benign hallucination, but the voice began telling them what to do. Their heavy obligation to obey the voice suggests significant distress or fear.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>Your Other has a firm hold of you (gain a Strand with your Other), and it's needy and wants to be in the driver's seat. While in your Breakdown, you are still able to rely on the Strands with your Other, but Exhausting one comes with a heavy request; it's hijacked your Id.</p><p><em>You regain your Stability when you successfully fulfill all of your personality's requests, or you forcibly gain control through the intervention of someone else.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you share an intimate moment with someone, Break a Strand with your Other and gain a Strand with that person.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you lock the Other you away and finally live for yourself and the real people around you, hope lives. Everyone around you gains an additional die to all of their actions for the scene, and every time they succeed on an action, your Stability and Ego go up by 1 (up to max).</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":1,"empathy":3}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot06","name":"The Hedgehog's Dilemma","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They may be struggling with significant emotional distress. Their sense of self-worth is barely an iota, leading to isolation and loneliness. They don't let anyone near them despite wanting to — feeling as though anyone who gets close will result in both of them being hurt.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>Nobody understands you or even wants to. Nobody loves you, as you are unable to be loved. Everyone hates you, especially yourself. You shut down and don't acknowledge anyone; it's better this way. You don't want to be hurt again or hurt others.</p><p><em>When someone shows you acceptance and tells you of your worth, regain your Stability.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment, ask yourself if you truly care for them. If you do, Break a Strand with them and push them away. If you don't, gain a Strand.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you realize you matter and want to fight for your existence, hope lives. You keep going even if you hit Durability 0 when you defeat an enemy and gain an additional dice with all combat rolls (this bonus stacks with each enemy defeated). If you manage to defeat your foes completely, gain a Strand with each of your teammates.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":1,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":2,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot07","name":"The Inferior Superior","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They may be experiencing significant pressure to maintain a certain image or reputation. They seem aware of their popularity and perceived qualities, but this image is fragile. They refer to themselves as 'A fragile mirror at the top', vulnerable to criticism or rejection.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>You thought you could show the others you could be something, but in reality, you are nothing, truly and fittingly nothing. Hide your insecurities, be sweet one minute, and be cruel the next. Put everyone around you down, and if you fail in their presence, let loose rage.</p><p><em>To successfully regain Stability, you must show someone special that they are trash beneath your heel, or truly admit what a failure you think you are to them.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment, ask them what they see in a perfect partner. If it matches the traits you see in yourself, gain a Strand.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you find someone who you know will accept you for who you truly are, hope lives. You cannot be contested; enemies' Ego Fields mean nothing to you. Enemies cannot reduce your damage with Ego Field for the rest of the battle.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":3,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":3,"wits":1,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot08","name":"The Hatred","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They may be exhibiting traits consistent with narcissism. They seem to derive a sense of power and control from dominating and manipulating others and may have little to no regard for the emotions or well-being of those around them. Their use of emotional cruelty as a weapon is particularly concerning.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>You've been telling yourself you're a monster, so why not finally commit to being one? Everyone is your enemy, and everyone deserves whatever is coming to them. Inflict pain on your enemies, inflict pain on your friends, inflict pain on anyone who ever dared to stand in your presence.</p><p><em>To regain Stability, someone more powerful than you must put you down. Power recognizes power.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment with someone, gain a Strand and Exhaust all your Strands with them. The next time you inflict pain against them, Refresh all your Strands with them.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you finally find someone you don't want to spurn, hope lives. All base damage you deal during this scene is doubled towards your foes. Every time you defeat an enemy, you may immediately roll to attack the nearest enemy. You gain this bonus till the danger passes.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":3,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":3,"wits":1,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot09","name":"The Thanatos","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They possess a powerful death drive perhaps rooted in feelings of guilt or shame. They are willing to throw themselves headlong into danger regardless of consequences. Their desire to die in a blaze of glory is particularly alarming.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>You become so ready for death that those around you are caught in the crossfire. You lash out, wanting their death and your own. If anyone stands in your way, they're dead to you.</p><p><em>You regain Stability when you solve an obstacle in your way with violence.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment with someone, decide if you care about the person. If you do, gain a Strand. If you don't, remove all Stress.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you decide to fight to protect rather than destroy, hope lives. For the remainder of the battle, the Stress cost on your Talents does not apply to you. You also reroll any 1s that come up on the dice once per roll (except Strand Die).</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":3,"agility":1,"wits":2,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot10","name":"The Puppeteer","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>They have a deep-seated need for control and power over others. They operate from the shadows, manipulating and orchestrating events to their liking. Their need for control may stem from past traumas, leading them to develop a manipulative and calculating personality.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>The time for games is over, no one will slight you again. You gather as much blackmail as possible and bring them all under your control; no one is safe from the strands you dangle them from. Every associate is just another chess piece on the board.</p><p><em>You regain your Stability when you offer peace to the one you've hurt the most.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you offer genuine regret for your actions towards someone, ask them if they forgive you. If they do, take a Strand and Refresh all the Strands you have with them. If they do not, take a Strand and Exhaust all the Strands you have with them.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you stop seeing your fellow pilots as chess pieces and start seeing them as humans, hope lives. First, Refresh all your Strands. Whenever a fellow pilot makes a roll during the battle, you may Exhaust a Strand to add an Automatic Success to their roll. This effect lasts until the danger is over.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":1,"empathy":3}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot11","name":"The Manufactured","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This individual is not a true human, but rather an android created for the sole purpose of piloting an Automata. They lack social skills due to the nature of their programming. Their creators may view them as a mere tool, replaceable and without inherent value beyond their usefulness.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>Your Automata leaks into your mind, and its desires are… different. It overrides your programming and injects itself as the 'superior' that you take your orders from. You operate as the Automata's eyes on the ground, carrying out its whims.</p><p><em>Regain Stability when someone realizes what's happened and takes measures to disconnect your mind from the Automata's.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment with someone, ask them if they see you more as a person or a machine. If they say a person, gain a Strand. If they say more as a machine, clear all Stress.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you embrace both sides of your identity and break free from your restraints, hope lives. For the remainder of this scene, 5s are now counted as successes on all your rolls and 6s count as doubles.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":1,"agility":2,"wits":3,"empathy":2},"statArrayB":{"strength":2,"agility":3,"wits":1,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot12","name":"The Legacy","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Their upbringing was rife with stories of heroic battles, with a family history steeped in military service. They were trained to fight from a young age but were never taught how to cope with the emotional toll of war. They see themselves as the last hope for their family's honor and their planet's survival.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>These Horrors have left you and your family scarred. You are a weapon, and you see yourself as nothing more than a tool to be pointed at the enemy. Respond to every situation with ruthless aggression, put your Bloodline before everyone, and resign yourself to your shackles.</p><p><em>You regain Stability when you reconnect with your Bloodline in a touching way or someone else shows you that you can be free.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you share an intimate moment with someone, consider them as part of your Bloodline and gain a Strand with them.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When you finally think of yourself and stand as your own person, hope lives. First, all rolls you make automatically gain an additional success upon succeeding. Second, whenever you deal damage to an enemy, you may Exhaust Strands for an equal amount of additional points of damage. Every time you destroy an enemy, Refresh a Strand.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":3,"agility":2,"wits":1,"empathy":1},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":1,"wits":3,"empathy":2}},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"EAPilot13","name":"The Forgotten","type":"pilot-archetype","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The subject suffers from a debilitating case of amnesia. They retain all typical motor skills and macro-level knowledge, but have no access to their past recollections. They have a strong connection to their Automata, with brain activity increasing when around their unit — an attachment that may border on unhealthy.</p>","breakdownText":"<p>Your amnesia has become too overwhelming; your mind is a fractured mirror, reflecting distortions of memories that once were. The world is a labyrinth, and you will be forever lost within it. Detach yourself from this reality, it's better if you just leave. Engage in self-destructive behavior to stop the noise.</p><p><em>You regain your Stability when you build yourself a new memory, a genuine connection separate from the past you.</em></p>","strandTalentDescription":"<p>When you have an intimate moment with someone, ask yourself whether they feel familiar or unfamiliar. If familiar, choose a Strand you already have that reminds you of them, gain an Exhausted Strand with them, and Refresh all associated Strands. If unfamiliar, gain a Strand with them.</p>","hopeTalentDescription":"<p>When everything finally clicks and comes together, hope lives. Your Ego and Ego Fields are restored to max, and you ignore all Ego costs on your Talents for the remainder of this scene. You also do not roll Ego Degradation rolls for the remainder of this scene.</p>","statArrayA":{"strength":2,"agility":1,"wits":1,"empathy":3},"statArrayB":{"strength":1,"agility":3,"wits":2,"empathy":1}},"flags":{}}
